THE worst drought Kenya has experienced in recent years is driving some depressed villagers to commit suicide.According to Red Cross officials in the East African country, an unspecified number of people have taken their lives, as they could not deal with the suffering. Kenya is currently facing a drought affecting millions struggling to find food.The drought has left 1,3 million people food insecure since December and has since escalated to more than 2 million in January. As of February, the figure has reached 2,7 million of Kenya&rsquo;s 46 million population. &ndash; CAJ NEWS